A Variational Autoencoder (VAE) is a type of generative model that learns to encode input data into a latent space and decode it back to reconstruct the original input data. 
VAEs are encoder-decoder models:

The encoder maps the input data to a distribution over the latent space.
The decoder samples from this latent space distribution reconstruct the input data.
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
What makes VAEs different from traditional autoencoders, is that VAE encourages the latent space to follow a known distribution (such as Gaussian). 
This makes them more useful for generating new data by sampling from this latent space.
